text: Life experiences have just been the  influences for the album
And just stuff that I’ve been through
Especially in the last five years
With being in the band and everything
It’s quite a personal album
And we recorded a lot of it actually
Out in the woods and stuff like this
Which is quite weird
It was just something that we wanted to do
Because we wanted to make it quite real and genuine
You know I used to listen to a lot of Bollywood being a kid
And stuff so yeah that definitely influenced the music a little bit
And then as I got older I guess I just started listening
To a lot of my dad’s old records like 90s stuff
Just like a lot of RnB and a lot of Rap
It’s a nice feeling to come out of a place
Where you are being told what to do
And to be upset because of certain expectations are set
And things that people want to see
It is just all my perspective and that’s fully liberating
I wouldn’t be able to give you like a one standout moment
Where I was like this is what I want to do
Because I guess I just always kind of knew
